            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>The Baltimore Convention: Cling to the Union</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Poem about the Baltimore Convention that states that "right is on our
                    [Douglas's] side."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>A Curious Coincidence</head>
                <origin>The Pennsylvania Gazette</origin>
                <commentary>"The advertiser was, doubtless, the ancestor of the present 'Abe
                    Lincoln,' the Black Republican candidate for President. All of his denunciations
                    of the slaveholder apply with equal force to his own grandsire."</commentary>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Reprint of a run-away slave ad from 1730 that names "Abraham Lincoln, of
                    Springfield" as the slave owner.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>More Treason</head>
                <origin>York Gazette</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Discussion of the forcible escape of Sherman M. Booth, who was imprisoned
                    for a violation of the Fugitive Slave Law. An "armed mob of Black Republicans"
                    seized him and helped him escape. The paper argues that this was treason and
                    holds the supporters of Lincoln responsible.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Amalgamation Case in Charlestown, Mass.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Discussion of a mixed marriage. A young Irish girl ran away with a black
                    man against the wishes of her parents.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
